AutoMoney Tool - 30 Day Development Roadmap
Day 1-3
- Set up Replit environment with Node.js
- Deploy and configure n8n instance on Replit (or via webhooks)
- Set up GitHub repo for version control and backups
Day 4-6
- Build basic web scraping workflows: Google Trends, Reddit, YouTube Trending
- Get Reddit API and YouTube Data API keys (free tier)
- Test data extraction and store output in Google Sheets (via API)
Day 7-10
- Integrate GPT-4 or OpenRouter free LLM for niche analysis
- Parse scraped data into prompt inputs for LLM
- Generate niche insights using GPT-4
Day 11-13
- Create web UI using Replit static site or GitHub Pages
- Enable category input and display niche results
- Auto-generate PDF report from results using Puppeteer or html2pdf
Day 14-17
- Schedule tasks via GitHub Actions or n8n cron triggers
- Add error handling and retry logic in workflows
- Log errors to Discord/Telegram via bots
Day 18-20
- Auto-generate SEO blog posts using GPT and long-tail keywords
- Auto-publish content to GitHub Pages blog or simple CMS
- Start building email list (e.g., Mailchimp or Firebase)
Day 21-25
- Integrate AdSense on blog and niche result pages
- Add contextual affiliate links (Shopify, SEMrush, etc.)
- Track clicks with UTM parameters and Bitly free tier
Day 26-30
- Optimize for multiple niches (fitness, pets, parenting, AI, finance)
- Add dropdown selector and dynamic keyword sources
- Test content generation and monetization logic across niches
